  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">F.a: Building resilient communities in the increasing extractive and non-extractive industry corporate area</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project is intended to enhance good governance and accountability of corporate companies involved in both the extractive and non-extractive industry and promote the respect of human rights, access to justice and civic participation of the vulnerable co
mmunities in the management of natural resouces. By promoting good governance and accountability of corporate companies, The project hopes to strengthen the capacity of communities to monitor and engage the private sector in the extractive and non-extracti
ve industries on issues of compliance to sector standards which in turn will increase capacities of the communities to monitor and engage the private sector (extractive and non-extractive) on compliance. The project will enhance the capacities of the natur
al resources adjacent communities to advocate for meaningful participation and equitable benefit, sharing in natural resources governance and management. www.tlc-uganda.org</narrative>
  </description>
